The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Fletcher role
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Fletcher role
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Former England coach and Zimbabwe captain Duncan Fletcher is to join the South African cricket team as a consultant as the Proteas prepare for the approaching Test series against Bangaldesh and Australia.         
	Cricket South africa (CSA) Monday announced that the Cape town-based Fletcher has linked up with the national team with immediate effect. The first Test starts in Bloemfontein on Wednesday followed by the second at Centurion from the following Wednesday.         
	Following these engagements Fletcher will travel with the team for the first Test against Perth in mid-December.                                                                                                                          
